The key insight is that for a localizing sequence `τ`, the stopped process agrees with `X` on the set where `τ > ⊥`, and the localizing sequence tends to `⊤` almost surely. So eventually, for each `ω` in a full measure set, the stopped process equals `X` at all times.

```lean
lemma Locally.rightContinuous
    (hX : Locally (fun X ↦ ∀ ω, Function.RightContinuous (X · ω)) 𝓕 X P) :
    ∀ᵐ ω ∂P, Function.RightContinuous (X · ω) := by
  filter_upwards [hX.IsLocalizingSequence.tendsto_top] with ω hω
  rw [WithTop.tendsto_atTop_nhds_top_iff] at hω
  obtain ⟨N, hN⟩ := hω ⊥
  have hτN : ⊥ < hX.localSeq N ω := hN N le_rfl
  have hstop := hX.stoppedProcess N ω
  intro i
  have hi : i ≤ hX.localSeq N ω := le_of_lt (lt_of_le_of_lt (WithTop.coe_le_coe.mpr bot_le) hτN)
  convert hstop i using 1
  rw [stoppedProcess_eq_of_le hi, Set.indicator_of_mem]
  exact hτN
```
